1 substitute teachers, and the day–to–day governance of prekindergarten providers
2 identified by the Council;
3 (2) the implementation of the requirements for publicly funded
4 prekindergarten programs under Chapter 165 of the Acts of the General Assembly of 2024;
5 (3) the method by which private prekindergarten providers are reimbursed
6 and whether a method of payment through forward funding would be a feasible alternative;
7 (4) inefficiencies in the invoicing process for private prekindergarten
8 providers and delays in private provider payments;
9 (5) whether the timeline for the operation of a prekindergarten educational
10 program required by the Prekindergarten Expansion Grant Program under §
11 7–101.2(c)(1)(iii) of the Education Article matches the typical needs of prekindergarten
12 students and parents;
13 (6) the feasibility of changing the Prekindergarten Expansion Grant
14 Program guidelines after grant agreements have been executed and whether there are
15 appropriate changes that should be made to the guidelines;
16 (7) the process through which quality rating levels in the Maryland
17 EXCELS Program are changed, including:
18 (i) disciplining a prekindergarten provider for an infraction by
19 lowering the quality rating level;
20 (ii) whether, when using a reduction of a prekindergarten provider’s
21 quality rating as a disciplinary measure, the reduction is commensurate with the severity
22 of the infraction;
23 (iii) the process for appealing a change in a prekindergarten
24 provider’s quality rating;
25 (iv) the feasibility of making standardized changes in the quality
26 rating level; and
27 (v) whether there are alternative methods available to address
28 infractions, including methods to deal with infractions caused by a single employee;
29 (8) the administrative processes that a private prekindergarten provider
30 must undertake in order to participate in publicly funded prekindergarten and whether the
31 processes could be streamlined or reduced;
32 (9) the feasibility of streamlining or reducing the administrative processes
33 for enrolling a child in publicly funded prekindergarten;

